<br>
You can in fact board the boat while it's stopped - I've done it.  You can also swim around a little bit from the dock, then board the boat at the furthest point from the pier you can and crank up invis - the skelly shouldn't come that far out.<br>
<br>
You can get around much of the outpost invisible, but as Numtini mentions some of the guards are undead Iksar (the others near the docks are DE Dragoons, not sure what else is around).<br>
<br>
A high-level SoW or Selo's with a drum can get you easily and quickly to the FM zone without trouble - you're going to fast to get aggro'd unless you step on a Sarnak's tail.  Just skirt the Outpost, pick up the road and head south.  When it turns east, look for the huge set of columns (you can't miss it!) and turn south again.  Run up to the ledge and through the pass to FM, and from there you can get to Lake of Ill Omen.<br>
<br>
FWIW, if I'm on Antonica and need to get to Kunark, I take this route rather than going to BBM and FV first.  Much faster in my opinion.<br>
<br>
At least one human agnostic bard reported not being KoS in the outpost.  Your mileage may vary.<br>
<br>
Dragoons occaisionally patrol the road between the outpost and the Frontier Mountain zone, particularly at night.<br>
<br>
I have heard that you can use Sneak (if you have it) to sell to the merchants - sneak first, approach from the side, and you'll be indifferent.  Haven't been brave enough to try it myself.<br>
<br>
By the mudhole, bards from about 20-24 can reportedly solo here using an all-instrument attack (see the Hunting Guide at www.eqdiva.com).  Might be possible from about 18th (when you get Denon's Disruptive Dischord) if you have decent armor.<br>
<br>
Also, the scorpion claws are a magical wind instrument, as good and possibly better than a minotaur's horn (which is +15% to your songs).  Data is inconclusive at last check.<br>
<br>
Nice guide, Num!<br>
<br>
Amerygn &quot;if I didn't travel so much, I'd be 30 by now&quot; <p>Amerygn D'Arundel<BR>
